# gulp-custom-sass

This is a simple Gulp task that allows you to customize SCSS frameworks without touching their source files.

I just didn't want to touch the source so that I could always install / update them without worrying that my work will be overridden.

Obviously you need Gulp.

## Install
```bash
npm install gulp-custom-sass
```

## Basic Usage

```js
var gulp = require('gulp');
var options = {

copyDir:"scss",
customDir:"custombootstrap",
customDirTarget:"bootstrap",
targetDir:"www/style",
mainCss:"main"

}

var customizer = require('gulp-custom-sass')(gulp,options);

gulp.task('default',['customizerMain'],function(){

});
```
